ce of Advancement at Chicago Office of Advancement at Peoria Office of Advancement at Rockford Office of Advancement at Urbana University of Illinois Foundation  Search for:    Research Home / Research  Research tlowery1 2019-06-04T13:15:08-05:00 College of Medicine: Research Our research goals are broad and ambitious, as are the needs and hopes of our patients. We aim to advance treatment now, and health in the future, by pursuing both fundamental insights and their application to the practice of medicine. Investigators across the College of Medicine are doing cutting-edge research in clinical medicine, in basic biomedical science, and in the translation of basic findings into clinical practice and societal health. Focus areas include cancer, women’s health, neurosciences, cardiac and vascular medicine, infectious disease, and obesity and diabetes. For campus specific information, please choose from below:  Research at Chicago  Research at Peoria  Research at Rockford  Research at Urbana Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research Click Here UI Collaboratory Research Profiles Click Here Research in the News UIC joins registry of COVID-19 frontline care providers, preventive drug trial  by Jacqueline Carey on April 30, 2020 at 5:00 pm Health care workers can now participate in HERO research program UIC helping the homeless combat COVID-19  by Jeffron Boynés on April 26, 2020 at 7:54 pm UIC helps an already vulnerable population deal with the effects of COVID-19 UIC to produce crucial material for COVID-19 testing  by Jacqueline Carey on April 24, 2020 at 6:00 pm UIC's Bellur S. Prabhakar is leading effort to produce 160,000 vials of Virus Transport Medium UI Health selected as first Vitalant convalescent plasma partner  by Jacqueline Carey on April 22, 2020 at 11:55 pm Convalescent plasma collection, treatments begin this week A biological mechanism for depression  by Jacqueline Carey on April 21, 2020 at 2:15 pm Location of a modified structural protein may identify depressed individuals 192 UIC medical students graduate early  by Jacqueline Carey on April 10, 2020 at 10:00 am New doctors ready to help during pandemic UIC clinical trials investigate COVID-19 treatments  by Jacqueline Carey on April 2, 2020 at 1:00 pm Trials study Ebola, rheumatoid arthritis drugs in hospitalized patients Board grants key approvals for UIC’s new health care, engineering buildings  by Jacqueline Carey on March 12, 2020 at 6:00 pm Project completion dates estimated for 2022 Sensing infection, suppressing regeneration﻿  by Jacqueline Carey on March 11, 2020 at 3:00 pm Study identifies how a DNA sensor regulates blood vessel repair Can ALS disease progression be slowed?  by Natasha Wadlington on March 5, 2020 at 7:05 pm Research may provide clues to slow down ALS Research Vice Chancellor for Research UI Collaboratory UNIVERSITY OF ILLINOIS College of Medicine UIC’s seven health sciences colleges and health care delivery enterprise. About  Education  Research  Patient Care  Departments  News  Giving INFORMATION FOR: Prospective and Current Students  Faculty & Staff  Alumni & Friends  Patients RESOURCES: UIC Directory  Blackboard  Emergency Information  Contact Us  Apply Now  Give  Contact Us Connect with us!    If you have questions, comments, or problems accessing this site, please E-mail the webmaster  © Copyright 2020 University of Illinois College of Medicine   | Privacy Statement College of Medicine | Chicago | Peoria | Rockford | Urbana                                                                                                                                        